File: A pair of handcuffs seen on a desk. JOHANNESBURG - Two more suspects have been arrested in connection with a drive-by shooting in Inanda last year. The incident, before an ANC meeting ahead of the local government elections, claimed three lives and left five others injured. An active ANC Member, Nomthandazo Mbeje, was arrested at her home in Bhambayi on Wednesday night. READ: Three women killed in Inanda drive-by shooting And the newly elected Ward 54 Councillor, Themba Mnguni, handed himself over after a warrant for his arrest was issued. The two appeared in court, facing charges of murder, attempted murder, and conspiracy to commit public violence. The community and different political parties protested outside the Ntuzuma Magistrate's Court. The case has been postponed until 11 February.